    "title": "Principal Plant Manager at Jindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates",
    "description": "Join the Jindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates family as a Plant Manager in Vadodara. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Jindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates:\nJindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage raw material procurement and inventory levels\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vadodara, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Jindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates!",
